<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>MECHANICAL ENGINEER</strong></span></h3>
<h4>Position Description:</h4>
<ul>
 	<li>Plan and design HVAC, plumbing and fire protection systems for commercial projects</li>
 	<li>Experience with electrical system design, including medium and low voltage distribution systems, communication systems, equipment selection, and short circuit and coordination analytical calculations is required.</li>
 	<li>Consult with clients to determine the scope of services required of a project</li>
 	<li>Conduct field surveys, analysis and selection of systems, evaluating project budgets</li>
 	<li>Prepare design documents and technical specifications</li>
 	<li>Coordinate work with team members, and participating in training for advanced skills development.</li>
</ul>
<h4>Qualifications:</h4>
A BSME is required and a PE is preferred with 5-10 years of hands-on design experience in HVAC and Plumbing. The ability to  work multiple projects concurrently is required. Strong people skills are a must.
<h1></h1>
<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>ELECTRICAL ENGINEER</strong></span></h3>
<h4>Position Description:</h4>
<ul>
 	<li>Electrical system design for lighting, power, and communications systems</li>
 	<li>Experience with electrical system design, including medium and low voltage distribution systems, communication systems, equipment selection, and short circuit and coordination analytical calculations is required.</li>
 	<li>Preparation and review of complex calculations such as short circuit and lighting (point to point) utilizing SKM Dapper/Captor and Lithonia Visual programs</li>
 	<li>Preparation of drawings using AutoCAD</li>
 	<li>Preparation and review of equipment and material specifications</li>
 	<li>Project schedule development</li>
</ul>
<h4>Qualifications:</h4>
A BSEE degree with at least 5 years of electrical engineering experience designing power and lighting system.

